          "body": "The chapter's closing scenes (4:18-22) are structured to demonstrate kingly authority. Jesus does not recruit through argument or audition. He commands — *follow Me* — and gives the promise that the calling will be transformative (*I will make you fishers of men*). The response is *immediately* (*eutheos*) in both cases: Peter and Andrew leave nets (means of livelihood); James and John leave boat AND father (vocation AND family loyalty). The dual *aphiemi* (leaving) is theologically weighty — when Christ stands fast against the devil's offer of the world (4:10-11), men are freed to walk away from lesser allegiances. The chapter ends with crowds *following* (4:25), but the crowds will thin; only the called will remain through chapters 26-27."
